    <etym xml:lang="ru">Может быть, отглагольное образование от не сохранившегося самостоятельно
        глагола %iaxs-%i в значении ‘ласкать’, ‘лелеять’ и пр. (%iaxs-gæ-jag%i → %iaxsgiag%i), ср.
        др.иран. основу <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w>axš-</w></mentioned> в <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>āxšti-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><lang/><w>āštī</w><gloss><q>мир</q></gloss></mentioned>; для развития значения ср.
        хотя бы <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/><w/><gloss><q>Friede</q></gloss></mentioned> —
            <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w/><gloss><q>Freund</q></gloss></mentioned>. Эту же
        основу мы готовы усмотреть в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_axston"/> ‘гнездо’, а
        закономерный ее вариант %iaz-%i (%i*axš-%i из %i*ag-s-%i) —- в д. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_azun"/> ‘давать приют’, ‘ласкать’ и в д. %iastʼonæ%i [<ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_axston"/>] (из %iaz-donæ%i) ‘гнездо’; см. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_azun"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_axston"/>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">Probable deverbal derivation from a verb %iaxs-%i, not preserved
        independently, with the meaning ‘caress’, ‘cherish’, etc. (%iaxs-gæ-jag%i → %iaxsgiag%i),
        cf. Old Iranian stem <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w>axš-</w></mentioned> in
            <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>āxšti-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><lang/><w>āštī</w><gloss><q>peace</q></gloss></mentioned>; for the development of
        meaning cf. at least <mentioned xml:lang="de"
            ><lang/><w/><gloss><q>Friede</q></gloss></mentioned> — <mentioned xml:lang=""
                    ><lang/><w/><gloss><q>Freund</q></gloss></mentioned>. We are ready to see the
        same base in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_axston"/> ‘nest’ and its natural variant %iaz-%i
        (%i*axš-%i из %i*ag-s-%i) in Digor <ref type="xr" target="#entry_azun"/> ‘give shelter’,
        ‘caress’ in Digor %iastʼonæ%i [<ref type="xr" target="#entry_axston"/>] (from %iaz-donæ%i)
        ‘nest’; see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_azun"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_axston"
        />.</etym>
